        "lang": "cht",
        "text": "照樣，我也願意女人以端正、嫻淑、自律為裝飾；不要以鬈髮、金飾、珠寶，或名貴衣裳為裝飾，"
      },
      "csbs": {
        "version_id": "CSBS",
        "version_name": "中文标准译本",
        "lang": "chs",
        "text": "照样，我也希望女人衣着端庄，以廉耻和自制来装饰自己；不以编发、金饰、珍珠或极其贵重的衣裳来装饰自己，"
      },
      "cunp": {
        "version_id": "CUNP",
        "version_name": "和合本新標點（神版）",
        "lang": "cht",
        "text": "又願女人廉恥、自守，以正派衣裳為妝飾，不以編髮、黃金、珍珠，和貴價的衣裳為妝飾，"
      },
      "esv": {
        "version_id": "ESV",
        "version_name": "English Standard Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "likewise also that women should adorn themselves in respectable apparel, with modesty and self-control, not with braided hair and gold or pearls or costly attire,"
      },
      "nasb": {
        "version_id": "NASB",
        "version_name": "New American Standard Bible",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "Likewise, I want women to adorn themselves with proper clothing, modestly and discreetly, not with braided hair and gold or pearls or costly garments,"
      },
      "niv": {
        "version_id": "NIV",
        "version_name": "New International Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "I also want the women to dress modestly, with decency and propriety, adorning themselves, not with elaborate hairstyles or gold or pearls or expensive clothes,"
      },
      "nkjv": {
        "version_id": "NKJV",
        "version_name": "New King James Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "in like manner also, that the women adorn themselves in modest apparel, with propriety and moderation, not with braided hair or gold or pearls or costly clothing,"
      },
      "nlt": {
        "version_id": "NLT",
        "version_name": "New Living Translation",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "And I want women to be modest in their appearance. They should wear decent and appropriate clothing and not draw attention to themselves by the way they fix their hair or by wearing gold or pearls or expensive clothes."
      }
    },
